dc_title_s: Taito, Formosa, Taito-cho, Taito-gun. A.M.S. L991
dc_description_s: AMS 1. North Decimal Degree 22.800000. South Decimal Degree 22.733333. East Decimal Degree 121.150000. West Decimal Degree 121.066667. Alternate title: Taito. In upper left margin: Formosa city plans 1:10,000. Polyconic projection. Relief shown by form lines and spot elevations. Compiled in 1945 from aerial photgraphy dated September and October 1944, by photo-planimetric method and by reference to Formosa 1:50,000, Sheet 2315-III (1944). Additional information from intelligence data. Place names are transcribed according to the modified Hepburn (Romaji) System. With a glossary. Name has been changed to T'ai-tung [Taitung]. Inset map shows air field near Sakura [Pinlang] (1:25,000).
dc_publisher_s: Washington, D.C. : Army Map Service, U.S. Army, 1945.
